humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The report indicates that multiple (2 of 27) right mid/low axillary lymph nodes are positive for metastatic carcinoma [AJCC pN2]. This means that the patient has metastases in 2 out of 27 axillary lymph nodes, which corresponds to N2 stage according to the AJCC staging system (New Rule 14).

humanMachineDialogue.text: The patient has 2 of 3 right axillary non-sentinel lymph nodes positive for metastatic carcinoma and 2 of 27 right mid/low axillary lymph nodes positive for metastatic carcinoma. This corresponds to AJCC pN2.
